text:
This is a problem where a jsp-generated java file will very infrequently be 
unable to compile, and a ClassCastException is thrown.  The jsp itself is fine 
(I'll include the generated java below) ie. restarting our webserver will allow 
this jsp to recompile successfully.  Also note that it is NOT specific to a 
particular jsp...every time this happens it is a different jsp than the one 
that I am reporting here.

Once in a while (perhaps once a week, utilizing 8 web servers and 1 million+ 
views) a ClassCastException is thrown.  This makes the affected server 
inoperable and we must restart it.  I'll simply put our server configuration 
down, and include the stack traces.

Please let me know if anyone takes a look at this?

We use:
1) JBoss 3.2.5
2) Apache 2.0.50
3) java jdk 1.4.2_05
